<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 17 at 10:51AM MDT  by NWS Pueblo</headline>
<description>...Bursts of Heavy Snow Through Midday...
A narrow band of heavy snow situated over the Boone and Fowler
areas will slowly move east through midday. Locations under this
heavier snow can expect significantly reduced visibility to
around one quarter mile at times, and snow covered roads. Those
traveling in this area, especially along the Highway 50 corridor,
should use caution and be prepared for hazardous driving
conditions. A diminishing trend with this snow with lessening
impacts are expected by early afternoon.</description>
